 thin slice of n (instances of watching, noticing, or making statements) contains not enough 
 information to allow for the guess of the individual variance-covariance terms. Asymptotics do 
 not help, since the problem gets worse as the sample size grows (an (unplanned/minor event) limit/guideline problem). In 
 sum, it will be necessary to force (on people) a structure on 
 the variance-covariance and to express it as a function of a small number of respected limits/guidelines. In 
 (related to space or existing in space) moving backward analysis, this is approached from 
 two main opinions, matching the data models 
 organized and listed in Section 4.1. In a geostatistics-clever 
 approach, the covariance is specified directly as a 
