 Leyland et al. (2000) and Leyland (2001). Error parts/pieces were introduced in (related to space or existing in space) econometric (detailed descriptions of exactly what is required) by Kelejian and Robinson (1995).20 
 Formally, the (related to space or existing in space) weights matrix is an n Ã-- n 
 positive matrix (W ) which specifies "neighborhood 
 sets" for each (instance of watching, noticing, or making a statement). In each row i, a non-zero 
 element wij defines j as being a neighbor of i. By 
 convention, an (instance of watching, noticing, or making a statement) is not a neighbor to itself, 
 so that the diagonal elements are zero (wii = 0). Note 
 that this definition is much wider than the term 
