 econometrics, the neighbors are touching (related to space or existing in space) 
 units, as in Fig. 1, but this can be easily generalized 
 to any network structure. For example, in Fig. 2, 
 the six (instances of watching, noticing, or making statements) are nodes on a network and the 
 existence of a neighbor relation matches the links between the nodes.21 The layouts in both Figs. 1 and 2 
 yield the same 6 Ã-- 6 (related to space or existing in space) weights matrix, illustrated 
